info:
Job Responsibilities 
• Provide desktop IT support including device deployment, OS installation, software configuration, and routine troubleshooting to ensure smooth office operations;
• Assist with daily operations and troubleshooting of enterprise networks, voice systems, server virtualization platforms (e.g., VMware, KVM, Hyper-V), and the Azure cloud environment;
• Draft and maintain various IT documents, including user guides, operation manuals, FAQs, and security baselines to support knowledge standardization;
• Participate in cybersecurity awareness initiatives by assisting in the design and execution of phishing simulations, weak password testing, and public Wi-Fi risk demonstrations using tools such as Kali Linux, Metasploit, and Burp Suite;
• Support privacy compliance projects by helping interpret and implement data security and privacy regulations, and assist in audit preparation and risk control.


Job Requirements 
• Currently enrolled in a university or above, preferably majoring in Computer Science, Information Security, or Network Engineering;
• Familiar with Windows operating systems and common office software, with basic skills in desktop device maintenance and troubleshooting;
• Familiar with server virtualization technologies (e.g., VMware, KVM, or Hyper-V) and the Azure cloud platform; hands-on experience is preferred;
• Understanding of voice communication protocols such as SIP is a plus;
• Strong interest in cybersecurity, with knowledge of TLS, weak password risks, and phishing attacks; hands-on experience with tools like Kali Linux, Metasploit, or Burp Suite is preferred;
• Familiarity with domestic and international laws and regulations related to network security, data protection, and privacy;
• Clear thinking, strong communication skills, a sense of responsibility, and the ability to draft technical documentation; available 2–4 days per week for 2–6 months; candidates available to start

Position Summary
Academic Advising is the process through which NYU Shanghai provides the necessary
resources for students to make good choices. The primary purpose of academic advising is to assist students as they develop meaningful educational plans compatible with their life goals. The intern will support the day-to-day operations of the Academic Advising Office by providing high-level administrative and clerical support. This position plays a critical role in maintaining office efficiency, coordinating communications, supporting academic advisors, and ensuring a welcoming and organized environment for students.

The main responsibilities include:
● Coordinate logistics for events such as study away events, team building, and the
monthly International Ed Luncheon. etc;
● Support communication efforts such as WeChat posting, weekly AA newsletters,
monthly ASP newsletters, and website updates;
● Assist in marketing initiatives and provide on-site support for advising related events
and programs. Work requires some hours in the evenings and weekends;
● Help manage triage during the walk-in hours;
● Other duties as needed.

Qualifications

Required Education
- Senior students, or Bachelor’s degree in Education, Counseling, or related academic field.

Preferred Experience
● Experience in administrative support, preferably in an academic setting;
● Experience working in higher education or student services.

Required Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities
● Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite, Google Workspace, Canva, and other visual
design tools;
● Strong organizational and time-management skills with keen attention to detail;
● Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
● Ability to adhere to strict confidentiality and other ethical standards.

工作内容：
1.参与服务端相关测试工作;
2.参与需求评审、代码review等工作, 并负责提出改进意见;
3.参与并跟进整个项目测试流程的实施, 及时记录和推动缺陷解决;
4.及时反馈测试进度和质量风险, 主动跟进并与产品研发排查过程中的问题, 确保项目按时按质交付。

任职要求：
1.本科及以上学历, 有软件测试实习经历优先;
2.至少了解Java或Python其中一种语言，能会写单元测试优先;
3.了解服务端测试, 接口自动化测试常用工具;
4.至少了解一种常用的数据库（MySQL、MongoDB、Sqlserver、oracle等），并能够编写常用SQL语句；
5.态度积极主动, 较强的自学能力, 能承担一定的工作压力, 有良好的逻辑思维能力和团队合作精神。

Position Summary

The NYU Shanghai and NYU Stern joint MS programs are one-year, full-time graduate degrees designed to equip students with globally competitive skills and regional expertise. Graduate Admissions at NYU Shanghai supports educational initiatives beyond the undergraduate level by overseeing the development and administration of the four NYU Shanghai–NYU Stern MS programs.

Graduate Admissions is looking for a highly organized and motivated individual to support the daily operation of the graduate office. The intern will be engaged in all affairs of the office, performing daily administrative tasks, and assisting with events and special projects. The intern will also contribute to long-term projects and interact with other school units, faculty, and students, depending on the changing needs of the office and their own creativity, initiative, and interests. 

This is a unique opportunity for students interested in the higher education sector to develop professional skill sets and gain a valuable global perspective in an enthusiastic and international working environment. 

Responsibilities
- Daily office operation: process expenses and reimbursement, track invoicing and payment, collate and organize documents, create and maintain databases for events and groups;
- Event support: assist in events such as student orientations, student activities, information sessions, and others;
- Other related responsibilities may from time to time be assigned by the operation team.

Qualifications
- Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively and independently in a cross-cultural environment;
- Proficiency in English required, with excellent speaking, writing, proofreading, and editing skills;
- Proficiency in Microsoft Applications, Google Docs/Apps, Qualtrics or other survey tools; 
- Basic skills in design software are required, including making event posters, presentation slides, and photo editing.
